    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1862-09-15T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1862-09-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="145"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d145">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                        Adams</persName>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 349.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State,</hi>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1862-09-15">
                            <hi rend="italic">September</hi> 15, 1862.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Sir: Since my previous despatches were put into the mail General McClellan
                    reports that the battle yesterday mentioned in his telegram proves to have been
                    a complete victory. The enemy was routed, and he fled during the night.
                    McClellan is in pursuit.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Charles Francis Adams,</hi> Esq., <hi rend="italic"
                            >&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
